paragraphs.title: Zeppelin Demo Notebook 2
paragraphs.text:
%md
Demonstrate loading, querying, visualizing, and saving the GroupLens MovieLens 100K Dataset dataset.
The 'MovieLens 100K Dataset' dataset available to download on [GroupLens](https://grouplens.org/datasets/movielens/100k/).

msg.data:
Demonstrate loading, querying, visualizing, and saving the GroupLens MovieLens 100K Dataset dataset.
The ‘MovieLens 100K Dataset’ dataset available to download on GroupLens.

paragraphs.title: Import Python Packages
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark import SparkFiles
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType, DateType

paragraphs.title: Load MovieLens Data from GroupLens
paragraphs.text:
%sh
DIR="ml-100k"
if [ -d $DIR ]; then
    echo "$DIR exist"
else 
    wget http://files.grouplens.org/datasets/movielens/$DIR.zip && unzip $DIR.zip
fi

# ls -alh $DIR

# copy from local file system (/var/lib/zeppelin) to the destination file system (/user/zeppelin)
hadoop fs -put -f  $DIR/u.* .
echo
hadoop fs -ls -h u.*

paragraphs.title: Load CSV Data into DataFrame
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
# u.data source schema: user id | item id | rating | timestamp
dataSchema = StructType([
    StructField('user_id', IntegerType(), True),
    StructField('item_id', IntegerType(), True),
    StructField('rating', IntegerType(), True),
    StructField('timestamp', IntegerType(), True)
])

ratingsDF = spark.read \
    .format("csv") \
    .option("header", "false") \
    .option("delimiter", "\t") \
    .load("u.data", schema=dataSchema)

ratingsDF.show(10, False)
ratingsDF.count()

paragraphs.title: Load CSV Data into DataFrame
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
# u.item source schema: movie id | movie title ...
itemSchema = StructType([
    StructField('movie_id', IntegerType(), True),
    StructField('title', StringType(), True)
])

itemsDF = spark.read \
    .format("csv") \
    .option("header", "false") \
    .option("delimiter", "|") \
    .load("u.item", schema=itemSchema)

itemsDF.show(10, False)
itemsDF.count()

paragraphs.title: Create Temporary View of Data and Query
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark

ratingsDF.createOrReplaceTempView("rating_table_tmp")

ratingsDF_2 = spark.sql("SELECT item_id, rating, user_id, CAST(timestamp as timestamp) as date_time " +
                          "FROM rating_table_tmp " +
                          "ORDER BY item_id, rating, user_id")

ratingsDF_2.show(10, False)
ratingsDF_2.count()

paragraphs.title: Replace Temporary View with New Query
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
ratingsDF_2.createOrReplaceTempView("rating")
itemsDF.createOrReplaceTempView("item")

topMoviesDF = spark.sql("SELECT i.title, AVG(r.rating) as avg_rating, COUNT(r.rating) as ratings " +
                        "FROM rating r, item i " +
                        "WHERE r.item_id = i.movie_id " +
                        "GROUP BY i.title " +
                        "ORDER BY avg_rating DESC, ratings DESC, i.title ASC")

print "Top 10 Movies"
topMoviesDF.show(10, False)

paragraphs.title: Native Zeppelin Visualization Based on SQL Query
paragraphs.text:
%sql
WITH tmp_table AS (
    SELECT i.title, AVG(r.rating) as avg_rating, COUNT(r.rating) as ratings
    FROM rating r
    JOIN item i ON (r.item_id = i.movie_id)
    GROUP BY i.title)
    
SELECT title, CAST(avg_rating AS DECIMAL(38,2)), ratings
FROM tmp_table
WHERE avg_rating >= ${avgRatingMin=4} AND ratings >= ${RatingsMin=2}
ORDER BY avg_rating ASC, ratings DESC, title ASC
LIMIT 25

paragraphs.title: Write, Read, Load Parquet Data
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
topMoviesDF.write.parquet('output/movies.parquet', mode='overwrite')
topMoviesPrqtDF = spark.read.parquet('output/movies.parquet')
topMoviesPrqtDF.orderBy(['avg_rating', 'ratings'], ascending=[0, 0]).show(10, False)
topMoviesPrqtDF.count()
